se. And one of them is going to choose you.=E2=80=9D <strong>Rudy Giuliani<=
/strong>, in New York, chose to enter office as a crime fighter. But the cr=
isis of 9/11 chose him. For Bass, the crisis not of her choosing was the fi=
res, and she lost her
credibility immediately when she refused to say something, <em>anything</em=
>, at the airport on the way back from Ghana. =E2=80=9CThat is now how ever=
ybody sees her and will always see her,=E2=80=9D the Democrat continued. =
=E2=80=9CShe obviously made the wrong choice of going in the first place, b=
ut she could have fixed all that by getting off the plane and at least sayi=
ng she cared.=E2=80=9D</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</=
p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">No one is standing up for Bass t=
hese days.
<strong>Kristin Crowley</strong>, her own fire chief, has thrown Bass under=
 the bus in numerous media appearances, accusing her of underfunding the de=
partment. The city=E2=80=99s controller, a 34-year-old gadfly C.P.A. named =
<strong>Kenneth Mejia</strong>, sided with Crowley, posting a lengthy socia=
l media review of Bass=E2=80=99s budget cuts. Meanwhile, Newsom conspicuous=
ly copied Bass on a letter announcing an investigation into the city=E2=80=
=99s water resources and fire preparation.</p><p style=3D"margin:0;
margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">And =
Newsom, a former mayor himself, expressed a flash of angry confusion during=
 a CNN interview with <strong>Anderson Cooper</strong> in the burning Palis=
ades last week, saying local officials needed to provide better answers abo=
ut the response. These are all obvious signals that Bass has zero political=
 capital left, much like <strong>Joe Biden </strong>after his disastrous de=
bate last summer. Bass has already announced for
reelection next year, a race she will almost certainly lose, possibly to Ca=
ruso, who came close to beating her last time, despite being a former Repub=
lican in a deep blue city. At the time, Bass didn=E2=80=99t have much of a =
campaign message beyond being the next Democrat in line, but she won with t=
he backing of an outside group organized by Hollywood mogul <strong>Jeffrey=
 Katzenberg</strong>, which ran ads portraying Caruso as a mini-<strong>Tru=
mp</strong>. <strong>Barack Obama</strong>
also gave Bass a final perfunctory lift, endorsing her late in the campaign=
 when Bass was struggling to close the deal with L.A. voters.=C2=A0</p><p s=
tyle=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-=
bottom:0px;">Caruso, who I=E2=80=99m told might run for governor of Califor=
nia next year, has been driving the political conversation here since last =
Tuesday night, when the fires began ripping through his own neighborhood of=
 the Palisades. Two years ago, Caruso portrayed Bass as a
feckless career politician who lacked any sort of big vision or experience =
to =E2=80=9Cfix=E2=80=9D Los Angeles. Feeling emboldened last week, Caruso =
called into FOX11 and lashed the mayor to host<strong> Elex Michaelson</str=
ong>. =E2=80=9CWe=E2=80=99ve got a mayor that=E2=80=99s out of the country,=
 and we=E2=80=99ve got a city that=E2=80=99s burning, and there=E2=80=99s n=
o resources to put out fires,=E2=80=9D Caruso proclaimed, immediately going=
 viral once the clip hit X. =E2=80=9CThis is absolute mismanagement by the =
city.=E2=80=9D=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0
</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">Again: Firefighters are<em> sa=
ying</em> they had enough water, and Caruso himself protected his gleaming =
Palisades mall with the help of private firefighters. The truth is still mu=
rky. But with Bass doing little to rally the city, frustrated Angelenos are=
 open to whatever Caruso is saying, especially since he ran for mayor, in p=
art, on expanding the fire department=E2=80=99s budget.=C2=A0</p><p style=
=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;">=E2=80=9C=
We=E2=80=99ll
never know if the outcome here would=E2=80=99ve been any less devastating u=
nder different leadership,=E2=80=9D said <strong>Josh Porter</strong>, a Pa=
lisades resident who lost his home in the flames last Tuesday, rushing out =
of the neighborhood with his two young children and dogs. =E2=80=9CBut we k=
now that we elect leaders to lead, especially in times of crisis. It=E2=80=
=99s been a week since this happened and the city has heard more from the g=
uy who lost to her than we have from her. Angelenos deserved to hear from a=
 leader
to assure them someone was driving the bus. Because it certainly didn=E2=80=
=99t feel that way.=E2=80=9D Porter told me that his wife was in London at =
the time the fires exploded, but she got back to LAX from overseas before t=
he mayor did.</p></div>
