line-height:150%;text-align:left;mso-line-height-alt:25.5px;"><p style=3D"m=
argin:0;margin-bottom:0px;"><em>My 2025 predictions (and mixing up
<strong>Logan</strong> and <strong>Jake Paul</strong>) sparked interesting =
conversations in my inbox. Some examples=E2=80=A6</em></p><p style=3D"margi=
n:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=
=E2=80=9CAs an animation producer and someone who=E2=80=99s been in the bus=
iness for three decades, I really hate your No. 23 prediction [that you] =
=E2=80=98wouldn=E2=80=99t be surprised if a full-length A.I.-generated anim=
ated film is acquired by a major distributor this
year.=E2=80=99 The talented creatives who work in animation, from the desig=
ners to the storyboard artists to the animators, can=E2=80=99t easily be re=
placed by generative A.I., and shouldn=E2=80=99t be. Animation is a collabo=
rative medium, and every artist who works on a project brings something uni=
que to it. Generative A.I. doesn=E2=80=99t think, and the result of someone=
 relying on A.I. to make an animated feature is going to be flat and uninsp=
ired. Audiences are going to pick up on that quickly, so here=E2=80=99s my =
prediction:
Animated shows and movies that have the tag =E2=80=98human-made=E2=80=99 wi=
ll outperform anything A.I.-generated.=E2=80=9D =E2=80=94<em>An animation p=
roducer</em></p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=
=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=E2=80=9CIt=E2=80=99s hard for me to tell =
what=E2=80=99s a prediction and what=E2=80=99s something that you know is h=
appening but you can=E2=80=99t say yet. [For instance], the NBC moves [you =
predict] are actually happening!=E2=80=9D =E2=80=94<em>An NBCUniversal empl=
oyee=C2=A0</em></p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">[<em>Ed. note</em>: That=E2=80=99s=
 why I said these predictions were based in part on my reporting!]=C2=A0=C2=
=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margi=
n:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=E2=80=9CYou know <strong>Zaz</strong> is gonna fli=
p-flop on <em>Sopranos</em> just because you said it will go to Netflix, ju=
st like he did on <em>West Wing</em> [which was pulled from Max and reinsta=
ted days later].=E2=80=9D =E2=80=94<em>A producer</em></p><p style=3D"margi=
n:0;
margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=E2=
=80=9C<strong>Lachlan</strong> [<strong>Murdoch</strong>, C.E.O. of Fox Cor=
p.] should tread very carefully on Fox Sports. His stock is up 33 percent i=
n the past six months in part because he has steadfastly kept his premium c=
ontent exclusive to the cable bundle, where it is still generating very str=
ong linear ratings, rather than licensing out NFL and Fox News to other str=
eamers. [A decision to put Fox Sports content on ESPN=E2=80=99s
coming Flagship service] might lead to a =E2=80=98fat check,=E2=80=99 as yo=
u put it, but Fox would further erode that linear bundle, thus damaging the=
 premium content assets it has paid so heavily to broadcast.=E2=80=9D =E2=
=80=94<em>An investor </em>=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px=
;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;">=E2=80=9CI love it when you conflate or=
 confuse the <strong>Pauls</strong>. Knowing the difference is about as imp=
ortant as distinguishing <strong>Zsa Zsa </strong>from <strong>Ava</strong>=
=2E=E2=80=9D =E2=80=94<em>A
non-industry reader</em></p></div>
